gomodel:SYNGO_1758  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: The localization of a Venus-tagged latrophilin-2 in knock-in mice in Fig. 1D-G shows a dendritic expression in CA1 with a dendrite domain-specific expression in the stratum lacunosum moleculare, where CA1 neurons receive inputs from entorhinal cortex.\nFig. 3D,E shows that latrophilin-2 localizes to dendritic spines in this stratum.\n\n1/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.\n- The resolution of the localization data in Fig.3 is insufficient to claim term 'integral component of postsynaptic membrane (GO:0099055)'. This is concluded from 1) its known role as a TM protein of the plasma membrane (Lphns are cell-adhesion molecules) and 2) the effect of postsynapse specific KD of the protein. Together this makes the selected term very plausible.. Experimental description: Knock-in mice were generated." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1758" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

